HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 33
BY REPRESENTATIVE BOYD
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Bishop-Elect Jonathan Everett on the occasion of his
elevation to the office of Bishop-Elect at Rock of Ages Baptist Church of New
Orleans
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Bishop-Elect Jonathan Everett on the occasion of his elevation to the office of
3 Bishop-Elect at Rock of Ages Baptist Church of New Orleans.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Bishop-Elect Jonathan Everett for his
5 dedication to ministry and to commend him on the occasion of his elevation to the office of
6 Bishop-Elect at Rock of Ages Baptist Church of New Orleans; and
7 WHEREAS, Bishop-Elect Everett is a son of the city of New Orleans who strives to
8 faithfully represent and give back to the community he was born in; he began as one of the
9 youngest youth leaders to be appointed by the Southern Baptist Convention and now serves
10 as the pastor of Rock of Ages Baptist Church; and
11 WHEREAS, at the time of Bishop-Elect Everett's appointment, Rock of Ages had
12 three faithful members; today, the congregation has grown to more than three thousand eight
13 hundred members, and the church is considered one of the fastest growing religious
14 institutions in Louisiana; and
15 WHEREAS, under Bishop-Elect Everett's leadership, Rock of Ages has become a
16 beacon of positivity in the city of New Orleans; the church sponsors large-scale food
17 giveaways, gas giveaways, and sneaker giveaways for school-aged children; the church hosts
18 an annual rally to support educators as they return to the classroom following summer break;
19 and
