1 WHEREAS, under Bishop-Elect Everett, Rock of Ages has supported local colleges
2 and universities, assisted members with becoming first-time homeowners, and provided
3 scholarships to parents returning to school to complete their education; and
4 WHEREAS, Bishop-Elect Everett has extended his ministry beyond New Orleans
5 and has become a sought-after speaker at domestic and international events; he has
6 ministered in numerous international locations, including the Bahamas, Mexico, Dominican
7 Republic, and Haiti, and has undertaken missions in regions including East Africa,
8 Colombia, and South America; he has also served as a speaker on numerous international
9 conference panels; and
10 WHEREAS, Bishop-Elect Everett has garnered the attention of local governments
11 and civic leaders, and his reputation has afforded him the opportunity to serve as a spiritual
12 advisor for past and present city officials, department heads, and state representatives; and
13 WHEREAS, Bishop-Elect Everett is the first African American to be appointed
14 overseer of the local retention rate initiative for students at the University of New Orleans;
15 he directs the mission work of the Merge Community Development Corporation, serves as
16 CEO and president of Prestige Environment Management Services, and sits on nonprofit
17 boards throughout the city; he also founded the iMatter Leadership Institute and authored
18 two books; and
19 WHEREAS, Bishop-Elect Everett received a bachelor of theology from Washington
20 Bible College; he is a devoted son to his mother, Wanda Everett; dedicated father to his son,
21 Jonathan Michael Everett, Jr.; and a brother to his eleven siblings; and
22 WHEREAS, Bishop-Elect Jonathan Everett is a guiding light for his congregation
23 and the New Orleans community, and he is most deserving of the highest recognition for his
24 dedicated ministry.
25 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
26 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Bishop-Elect Jonathan Everett on the
27 occasion of his elevation to the office of Bishop-Elect at Rock of Ages Baptist Church of
28 New Orleans and does hereby extend sincere wishes that he remain prosperous as he begins
29 a new chapter in his ministry.
